hasAttributes.name: locationAlias3

hasAttributes.name: locationNumber
hasAttributes.description: Unique code or number identifying the location to its users.

hasAttributes.name: locationPositionAltitude
hasAttributes.description: Altitude. The value domain and the interpretation are the same as for the text of the altitude element in KML (see notes below)

hasAttributes.name: locationPositionLatitude
hasAttributes.description: Latitude. The value domain and the interpretation are the same as for the text of the latitude element in KML

hasAttributes.name: locationPositionLongitude
hasAttributes.description: Longitude. The value domain and the interpretation are the same as for the text of the longitude element in KML

hasAttributes.name: managingOrganization
hasAttributes.description: The organization responsible for the provisioning and upkeep of the location.

hasAttributes.name: mode
hasAttributes.description: Indicates whether a resource instance represents a specific location or a class of locations.

hasAttributes.name: operationalStatus
hasAttributes.description: The Operational status covers operation values most relevant to beds (but can also apply to rooms/units/chair/etc such as an isolation unit/dialysis chair).

hasAttributes.name: partOf
hasAttributes.description: Another Location which this Location is physically part of.

hasAttributes.name: physicalType
hasAttributes.description: Physical form of the location, e.g. building, room, vehicle, road.

hasAttributes.name: status
hasAttributes.description: The status property covers the general availability of the resource, not the current value which may be covered by the operationStatus, or by a schedule/slots if they are configured for the location.

hasAttributes.name: type
hasAttributes.description: Indicates the type of function performed at the location.

definitions.description: Details and position information for a physical place where services are provided and resources and participants may be stored, found, contained or accommodated.
